theorem interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure A)))))))))) =
      interior (closure A) := by
  -- Start with the six-step idempotence lemma.
  have h₆ :
      interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure A)))))))) =
        interior (closure A) := by
    simpa using
      interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_eq
        (X := X) (A := A)
  -- Apply one more `interior ∘ closure` to both sides of `h₆`.
  have h₇ :
      interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure A)))))))))) =
        interior (closure (interior (closure A))) := by
    simpa using congrArg (fun S : Set X => interior (closure S)) h₆
  -- Collapse the remaining two alternating applications.
  have h₂ : interior (closure (interior (closure A))) = interior (closure A) :=
    interior_closure_interior_closure_eq (X := X) (A := A)
  simpa [h₂] using h₇

theorem interior_subset_closure_interior_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
  intro x hxIntA
  -- Step 1: `x` lies in `interior (closure A)` because interiors are monotone
  have hxIntClosureA : x ∈ interior (closure A) :=
    Topology.interior_subset_interior_closure (A := A) hxIntA
  -- Step 2: every point of `interior (closure A)` lies in
  --         `closure (interior (closure A))`
  have hIncl : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
    intro y hy
    exact subset_closure hy
  -- Finish by combining the two facts
  exact hIncl hxIntClosureA
